<font color="#FF0000">A BURNING MEMORY</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb  9 21:40:36 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Sliding off the chopper<br>
old before my time<br>
searching for my brothers<br>
caught behind the line<br><br>
all alone in presence<br>
followed by my mind<br>
didn't think I'd see twenty<br>
the justice sure was blind<br><br>
my body was on auto <br>
drained from lack of sleep<br>
but the callus stare my eyes set forth<br>
showed my wounds were deep<br><br>
didn't want to care again<br>
lives kept drifting by<br>
couldn't seem to cry any more<br>
my heart was cold, my eyes were dry<br><br>
slipping through the jungle floor<br>
blending with the scene<br>
coming upon a hideaway<br>
nestled in the green<br><br>
cautiously I approached<br>
not sure what I would find<br>
lifting the thatched leaves and limbs<br>
the vision burning in my mind<br><br>
there they were, the men I sought<br>
hoping to survive<br>
their eyes told me a story <br>
and today it's still alive<br><br>
Deep within our spirit<br>
is the child that we once knew<br>
The innocence and zest for life<br>
of that spirit pure and true<br><br>
The turmoil of life's journey can lock it all away<br>
and never find the understanding needed to soar day by day<br><br>
There are too many who will never <br>
understand where I have been.<br><br>
But I understand and accept myself ...<br>
and live life with the wind.
